content: As of 12/12/2020 the app is built for an out-of-date version of Android and does not work correctly. The version I use is Android 11, so I can't use the app.

I don't really like it. I would like to see the results of my diary card all in one place. As it is you have to open up each category separately- emotion, behavior, and skills. And open up each subcategory separately. I would also like to see the definitions of terms as I am filling it out.
For traditional DBT diary card spot on! It takes a little bit of getting used to, but the closest Android version I found to the original DBT diary card.
I wish there was an option to customize the options to select from as far as behaviors.
I like the app. I find it every helpful and simple to us. Very relevant to the goal of being more in control of myself.
If you are using this in conjunction with DBT therapy, using the latest book from Marsha - BEWARE! This app is outdated and unusable.
I'd really like the ability to go back and fill in diary cards. Right now if you miss a day it had an angry red "1MISSED DAY."
That's the main reason I needed it and now it doesn't work
I'd like the ability to sync across multiple devices. Possibly add a login option.
As soon as I can print out diary cards, I'll give it 5 stars.

Am studying DBT...I like the app though it is very basic. I would suggest the developer look over the diary cards, as Behaviours and Skills are missing core concepts, and doubling up on others (typos I think?)
Unsatisfactory app, and there was no option for a refund. Buyer beware.
